---
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';

const lang = 'en' as const;
const title = 'Polvo Eres';

const img1 = (await import('../../../assets/images/obras/polvo-eres/polvo-eres-01.jpg')).default;
---

<Layout
  lang={lang}
  title="Polvo Eres — Work"
  description="Polvo Eres (2024). Wall carving — brick, plaster, paint, ~60x400cm, MAMU. Maria Elvira Escallon."
>

  <article class="work-page">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Header -->
      <header class="work-page__header">
        <p class="label">Work / 012</p>
        <h1>{title}</h1>
        <p class="work-page__meta">2024 &nbsp;/&nbsp; Wall carving — brick, plaster, paint &nbsp;/&nbsp; ~60 x 400 cm</p>
      </header>

      <!-- Main gallery -->
      <div class="work-page__gallery">
        <img src={img1.src} alt="Polvo Eres — Words carved into museum wall, exposing brick and plaster layers" loading="eager">
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: Polvo Eres — Detail of carved lettering and debris at floor level ]</div>
        <div class="placeholder-img" style="aspect-ratio:16/10;">[ Pending: Polvo Eres — Installation view at MAMU ]</div>
      </div>

      <!-- Video -->
      <div class="work-page__video">
        <div class="work-page__video-header">
          <h3>VIDEO</h3>
          <span class="label">Polvo Eres · Video · 2:00 min</span>
        </div>
        <video controls preload="metadata" poster="">
          <source src="/maria-elvira-escallon/video/polvo-eres-obra.mp4" type="video/mp4">
          Your browser does not support HTML5 video.
        </video>
      </div>

      <!-- Text + Technical sheet -->
      <div class="work-page__body">
        <div class="work-page__text">

          <p class="curatorial">
            Words carved directly into a museum wall, exposing internal layers — beneath
            white paint, the brick layer is revealed — while debris accumulates at floor
            level. The biblical phrase "Thou art dust and unto dust thou shalt return"
            is inscribed not on the wall's surface but into its body, requiring the
            destruction of the wall itself to make the text legible.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The act of carving reverses the usual relationship between writing and its
            support. Rather than adding material (ink, paint) to a surface, Escallon
            removes material, creating text through subtraction. The words emerge from
            the wall's own substance — plaster, brick, the accumulated layers of
            institutional architecture — making the medium and the message inseparable.
          </p>

          <p class="curatorial" style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The debris that falls to the floor as the carving proceeds becomes part of
            the work: a material enactment of the very phrase being inscribed. The dust
            from which we come and to which we return is not merely invoked but produced,
            accumulating beneath the text as its inevitable byproduct. The wall itself
            begins its return to dust in the act of speaking about it.
          </p>

          <h3 style="margin-top: var(--s4);">CONTEXT</h3>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            Presented at MAMU in 2024, <em>Polvo Eres</em> is a site-specific intervention
            that will be destroyed when the exhibition ends and the wall is repaired or
            demolished. This built-in impermanence reinforces the work's meditation on
            mortality and the transience of all material forms — including the museum wall
            that typically serves as a neutral, permanent backdrop for art.
          </p>
          <p style="margin-top: var(--s2);">
            The work connects to Escallon's broader investigation of institutional
            architecture as material rather than mere container, and to her sustained
            engagement with processes of decay, erosion, and return to elemental states
            — themes present across works from <em>In Memoriam</em> to <em>Precipitacion
            de Arenas</em>.
          </p>
        </div>

        <aside class="work-page__ficha">
          <h4>TECHNICAL SHEET</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            <strong>Polvo Eres</strong><br>
            2024<br><br>
            Wall carving.<br>
            Brick, plaster, paint.<br><br>
            ~60 x 400 cm<br>
            Site-specific, MAMU
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">EXHIBITIONS</h4>
          <div class="ficha">
            Encounters in the Dust Factory — MAMU, 2024
          </div>

          <h4 style="margin-top: var(--s3);">HOW TO CITE</h4>
          <div class="ficha" style="font-size: 0.65rem;">
            Escallon, M.E. (2024). <em>Polvo Eres</em>.
            Wall carving. Available at:
            mariaelviraescallon.com/en/works/polvo-eres/
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>

<style>
  .work-page {
    padding-top: calc(var(--s5) + 40px);
  }

  .work-page__header {
    margin-bottom: var(--s4);
  }

  .work-page__header h1 {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    margin: var(--s1) 0;
  }

  .work-page__meta {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--ash);
    letter-spacing: 0.03em;
  }

  .work-page__gallery {
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--s2);
    margin-bottom: var(--s4);
  }

  .work-page__gallery img {
    width: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .work-page__body {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 2fr 1fr;
    gap: var(--s5);
    margin-bottom: var(--s5);
  }

  .work-page__text h3 {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--ash);
    padding-bottom: var(--s1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);
  }

  .work-page__ficha h4 {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.6rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.15em;
    color: var(--ash);
    margin-bottom: var(--s1);
    padding-bottom: var(--s1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--paper-dark);
  }

  .placeholder-img {
    width: 100%;
    background-color: var(--paper-dark);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    color: var(--ash-light);
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.55rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
  }

  .work-page__video {
    margin: var(--s4) 0;
  }
  .work-page__video-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: baseline;
    margin-bottom: var(--s2);
    padding-bottom: var(--s1);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--ink);
  }
  .work-page__video-header h3 {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .work-page__video video {
    width: 100%;
    background: var(--ink);
    display: block;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .work-page__body {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
